column23: FlavourText
Give up your flesh unto the gods, and in vulnerability find strength.
Burn the spirit to vitalise the flesh.
You may live forever, so long as someone remains to be sacrificed.
As true belief fades, the facade of faith grows, leaving you powerful but hollow.
Wreathed in madness and blood, you are unstoppable.
Tasalio and Valako test you, child of the volcano. Prove yourself worthy.
Utter trust in your defence unleashes ultimate potential.
No man may enslave you, for you have a secret: you're always angry.
Invite the enemy when you are strong, evade them when you are weak;\r\nstrike with the coming of the storm.
The fewer there are, the less you have to share.
You circle the black scorpion with enmity, daring it time and again.
Speak not, but listen, for danger reveals itself on the wind.
Put your faith in intellect rather than mysticism.
Master the mortal world, and you may find immortality beyond.
Your every move is calm and calculated with absolute certainty.
Empowered by the divine, you fear no weapon of man.
You may find that having is less pleasing a thing than wanting.
Your fiery passion inspires everyone around you - especially your foes.
You are the heart of the empire, shining bright so that all are lifted up by your light.\r\nLet none tell you otherwise.
Displays of power are not just for show. If you are never truly tested,\r\nyou may divert those resources elsewhere.
